The paper deals with variable-length compression, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also considers side-information available at both encoder and decoder, which is a common theme in coding theory (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes new information quantities, which could be relevant to data structures (cs.DS) and statistical inference (cs.SI).
